GPIO Port
--------------

|Product| has a 10 Pin 3.81mm **GPIO Connector**, as shown in the figure below.
The :ref:`table <gpio-table>` below gives details about the definition of every Pin.

.. figure:: /Media/Pi/A53/Others/GP_IO.jpeg
   :align: center
   :figclass: align-center

   *GPIO Connector*


.. _gpio-table:

.. table:: GPIO Connector Pin-out
   :align: center
   :width: 100%
   :widths: auto

   +---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
   | .. centered:: GPIO Connector Pin Definition:                                                                                    |
   +======================================+=============================+============================================================+
   | **Pin Number**                       | **Definition**              | **Description**                                            |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
   | Pin 10                               | VCC                         | Isolated Power +5V Output                                  |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
   | Pin 9                                | GND                         | Isolated Ground                                            |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
   | Pin 8                                | OUT1                        | Isolated Output 1                                          |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
   | Pin 7                                | OUT2                        | Isolated Output 2                                          |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
   | Pin 6                                | OUT3                        | Isolated Output 3                                          |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
   | Pin 5                                | OUT4                        | Isolated Output 4                                          |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
   | Pin 4                                | IN1                         | Isolated Input 1                                           |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
   | Pin 3                                | IN2                         | Isolated Input 2                                           |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
   | Pin 2                                | IN3                         | Isolated Input 3                                           |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
   | Pin 1                                | IN4                         | Isolated Input 4                                           |
   +--------------------------------------+-----------------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+

.. attention::

   + The GPIO has been Opt-Isolated and it uses the 5V Logic by default. You can use an external isolated power input but the power input range should be from 5V to 24V DC.
   + The 4 output channels can drive at most 500mA current on each channel.